Description: Small limestone vase with pointed base and elongated drop-shaped body with moulded everted rim, much of which is now missing.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Dr David George Hogarth
Bibliographic references: Zitman 2010 / The necropolis of Assiut: a case study of local Egyptian funerary culture from the Old Kingdom to the end of the Middle Kingdom (I, 89)
